{"cursor":"14137","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Vice' is a practice or a behavior or habit generally considered immoral,\ndepraved, or degrading in the associated society. In more minor usage, vice can\nrefer to a fault, a negative character trait, a defect, an infirmity, or a bad\nor unhealthy habit (such as an addiction to smoking). Synonyms for vice include\nfault, depravity, sin, iniquity, wickedness, and corruption.\n\nThe opposite of vice is virtue. {{cite web| url=\nhttp://thesaurus.com/browse/vice|title= Vice |publisher=Thesaurus.com|accessdate=2012-30-\n06}}\n","linknr":246,"url":"Vice","recorded":1362890421,"links":26,"instances":["catholic_church","deadly_sin","philosophy","religious_views","psychology"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Habits","Morality","Vices"],"headings":["Etymology","Law enforcement","Religion","Emotions as vices","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Stiftskirche_Niederhaslach_Glasfenster_%28Kampf_der_Tugenden_mit_dem_Laster%29.jpg/250px-Stiftskirche_Niederhaslach_Glasfenster_%28Kampf_der_Tugenden_mit_dem_Laster%29.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["habit","psychology"],["love","religious_views"],["sacrament_of_penance","catholic_church"],["sloth","deadly_sin"],["golden_mean","philosophy"]],"members":["sacrament_of_penance","sloth","golden_mean","love","habit"],"related":["Habit_(psychology)","Morality","Addiction","Smoking","Virtue","English_language","Latin","Deputy","Vice_p